[[File:Ben Best lecture.jpg|thumb|Ben Best giving a lecture to high school students at the [[Cryonics Institute]].]]
'''Ben Best''' was President and CEO of the [[Cryonics Institute]], the world's second largest [[cryonics]] organization, for nine years (between 2003 and 2012). Best is a well-known activist in [[cryonics]] and [[life extension]] advocacy.<ref>{{cite web | last = Greenhouse | first = Kim | title = Cryonics and the State of the Industry | work = Radio interview with Ben Best | publisher = The Rainmaking Company | date = 20 January 2010 | url = http://itsrainmakingtime.com/2010/cryonics/ | accessdate = 28 November 2012 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130102140705/http://itsrainmakingtime.com/2010/cryonics/ | archivedate = 2 January 2013 | df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = de Wolf | first = Aschwin | title = Interview with Cryonics Institute president Ben Best | work = Depressed Metabolism | publisher = Evidence-based Cryonics   | date = 6 August 2008 | url = http://www.evidencebasedcryonics.org/2008/08/06/interview-with-cryonics-institute-president-ben-best/
  | accessdate = 28 November 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = A tour of the Cryonics Institute in Clinton Township | newspaper = DETROIT NEWS |  publisher = YouTube | date = 4 January 2010 | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o7hf4BkSgwY | accessdate = 14 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Bär | first = Nora | title = En el futuro podremos vivir mil años (In the future we will live a thousand years) | publisher = LA NACION (lanacion.com) | date = 1 June 2012 | url = http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1478176-en-el-futuro-podremos-vivir-mil-anos | accessdate = 28 November 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Maldonado| first = Nicolas | title = Congelamiento de cuerpos: el sueño de la vida después de la muerte (Freezing of bodies: the dream of life after death) | publisher = EL DIA | date = 1 June 2012 | url = http://www.eldia.com.ar/edis/20120602/congelamiento-cuerpos-sueno-vida-despues-muerte-informaciongeneral0.htm | accessdate = 28 November 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | author = Deutsche Gesellschaft für Angewandte Biostase e.V | title = Applied Cryobiology – Scientific Symposium on Cryonics | work = Symposium 2010 | publisher = German Society for Applied Biostasis (DGAB) | date = 2 March 2013 | url = http://www.biostase.de/us/symposium2010.html | accessdate = 14 October 2013 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131007123728/http://www.biostase.de/us/symposium2010.html | archivedate = 7 October 2013 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vXcHD5hFj50 (YouTube Video of German conference)] He holds undergraduate degrees in [[pharmacy]] from the [[University of British Columbia]], and physics and computing science (BSc), and finance (BBA) from [[Simon Fraser University]] in British Columbia, Canada. Best is also certified as a [[National Association of Parliamentarians#Levels|Professional Registered Parliamentarian]] by the [[National Association of Parliamentarians]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Members List | work = Plantation Unit of Parliamentarians | publisher = ORGSITES.COM  | date = 1 September 2012 | url = http://www.orgsites.com/fl/p-u-p/index.html | accessdate = 1 March 2013}}</ref> He currently works for the [[Life Extension Foundation]].<ref name="LEF">{{cite web | last = Faloon | first = William | title = Conference Report: Ellison Medical Foundation Colloquium on Aging | work = Preamble | publisher = [[Life Extension Foundation]]  | date = January 2013 | url = http://www.lef.org/magazine/mag2013/jan2013_Conference-Report-Ellison-Medical-Foundation-Colloquium-on-Aging_01.htm | accessdate = 1 March 2013 }}</ref>

