{{Infobox Officeholder |name = Erhart Aten |image = |caption = |order = [[Governor of Chuuk State]] |lieutenant = [[Bob Mori]] |term_start = October 1978 |term_end = May 8, 1986 |predecessor = office created |successor = [[Gideon Doone]] |birth_date = 1932 |birth_place = |death_date = {{death year and age|2004|1932}} |death_place = Chuuk lagoon, [[Chuuk State|Chuuk]], [[Federated States of Micronesia]]|party = |spouse = |alma_mater = }}
'''Erhart Aten''' (1932–2004) was a [[Federated States of Micronesia|Micronesian]] [[politician]] who served as the first elected [[Governor of Chuuk State|Governor of]] [[Chuuk State]] (then called Truk).<ref name=xavier> {{cite news|first=|last=|title=Alumni Profiles|url=http://xaviermicronesia.org/alumni/alumni-profiles|work=[[Xavier High School (Micronesia)]] |publisher=|date= |accessdate=2011-02-11}}</ref> Aten took office in 1978 after self-government was implemented.<ref name=rnzi/> He stepped down from office in 1986 after serving two, four-year terms as Governor<ref name=nu> {{cite news|first= |last= |title=101 Candidates Run for Office in Truk |url=http://www.comfsm.fm/library/digitallibrary/V7N41986.pdf |work=[[The National Union]] |publisher= |date=1986-03-28 |accessdate=2011-02-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326214558/http://www.comfsm.fm/library/digitallibrary/V7N41986.pdf |archivedate=2009-03-26 |df= }}</ref> and was succeeded by [[Gideon Doone]].<ref name=xavier/> Aten graduated from [[Xavier High School (Micronesia)|Xavier High School]], a [[Jesuit]] [[secondary school]] located on Chuuk, in 1962.<ref name=xavier/>
In late November 2004, Aten and three other men were crossing Chuuk lagoon to [[Weno]] island when their boat was hit by a storm.<ref name=rnzi> {{cite news|first=|last=|title=Former Chuuk governor still missing at sea |url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=13687|work=[[Radio New Zealand International]] |publisher=|date=2004-12-09 |accessdate=2011-02-11}}</ref> Their boat and all on board were lost at sea.<ref name=rnzi/>
