'''Henry Chamberlain''' (died about 17 April 1888) was a member of the [[New Zealand Legislative Council]] from 8 February 1869 to 17 April 1888, when he died.<ref>{{cite book |last= Wilson |first= James Oakley |title= New Zealand parliamentary record, 1840-1984 |accessdate= |edition= 4 |origyear= First ed. published 1913 |year= 1985 |publisher= V.R. Ward, Govt. Printer |location= Wellington |isbn= |oclc= 154283103 |page=151}}</ref><!-- Wilson has 17 April tho he was found on 15th or 16th -->

He was from Auckland. He had fallen into a water-hole on a property of his near [[Drury, New Zealand|Drury]] and drowned; he was reported as having been prospecting for coal.<ref> ''Star'' 16 April 1888 p3; ''Waikato Times'' 17 April 1888 p2 </ref>

