[[File:Torrington Gopher Hole Museum.jpg|thumb|Scene from the Gopher Hole Museum, Torrington Alberta, Canada]]
The '''Torrington Gopher Hole Museum''', located in [[Torrington, Alberta|Torrington]], [[Alberta]], features stuffed gophers ([[Richardson's ground squirrel]]s) posed to resemble townspeople.<ref>[http://thegauntlet.ca/story/3196 "The Torrington Gopher Hole Museum"]. ''The Gauntlet'', September 16, 1999.</ref> It was opened in 1996.
The museum is profiled in [[Chelsea McMullan]]'s 2015 documentary film ''[[World Famous Gopher Hole Museum]]''.<ref>[http://realscreen.com/2015/08/05/tiff-15-al-purdy-omar-khadr-make-canadian-line-up/ "TIFF ’15: “Al Purdy,” “Omar Khadr” make Canadian line-up"]. ''Realscreen'', August 5, 2015.</ref>
